notesStmt.note: Title from spine; listed in Zacour-Hirsch as Recueil de poësie.

msContents.summary: Collection of chansons and airs, many on romantic themes, with an alphabetical title index at the end.

supportDesc.extent: 377 leaves : 252 x 190 (209 x 145) mm. bound to 261 x 205 mm

layoutDesc.layout: Frame-ruled in ink, with poems written in irregular single or double columns.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in a cursive script by many hands.

binding.p: Contemporary calf (Zacour-Hirsch), gold ornamentation on spine.

origin.p: Written in France in the late 17th and early 18th centuries.
